pasted-image.tiff
Social psychologists have focused on how gender boundaries are policed, with those who challenge gender norms facing discipline for stepping out of bounds.
In such situations, symbolic boundaries become institutionalized into social boundaries.
Similarly, groups police themselves to follow traditional gender norms.

Gender in particular is an area where fruitful studies of boundary crossing and shifting can be done, due to a greater (if still limited) willingness to accept gender fluidity than class or race fluidity.
